st (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Father of Elizabeth Fryar was born about 1180, in Scotland. He married Mother of Elizabeth Fryar about 1200, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in his hometown, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"about 1180–":"umbes 1180–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1207–Female":"1207–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","about 1180":"umbes 1180","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1207":"1207","1180":"1180","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1180–":"noin 1180–Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1207–Female":"1207–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","about 1180":"noin 1180","about 1200":"noin 1200","1207":"1207","1180":"1180","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1180–":"environ 1180–Décédé","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","1207–Female":"1207–Décédée","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","about 1180":"environ 1180","about 1200":"environ 1200","1207":"1207","1180":"1180","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"Father of Elizabeth Fryar est né environ 1180, à Écosse. Il a épousé Mother of Elizabeth Fryar environ 1200, à Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé dans sa ville natale, et a été enterré à Écosse."},"de":{"about 1180–":"um 1180–Verstorben","1180–Female":"1180–Verstorben","1207–Female":"1207–Verstorben","1180–Male":"1180–Verstorben","about 1180":"um 1180","about 1200":"um 1200","1207":"1207","1180":"1180","Scotland":"Scotland","lifeSummary":"Father of Elizabeth Fryar wurde um 1180 in Scotland geboren. Er hat um 1200 in Scotland Mother of Elizabeth Fryar geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb in seinem Geburtsort und wurde in Scotland begraben."},"ht":{"about 1180–":"about 1180–Desede","1180–Female":"1180–Desede","1207–Female":"1207–Dese